APP1-0000.Name: VersionID
APP1-0000.Description: Version of the Global Positioning Systems (GPS) IFD, given as 2.0.0.0. This tag is mandatory when the GpsIFD tag is present. When the version is 2.0.0.0, the tag value is 0x02000000.

APP1-0001.Name: LatitudeRef
APP1-0001.Description: Indicates whether the latitude is north or south latitude. The ASCII value 'N' indicates north latitude, and 'S' is south latitude.

APP1-0002.Name: Latitude
APP1-0002.Description: Indicates the latitude. The latitude is expressed as three RATIONAL values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively. When degrees, minutes and seconds are expressed, the format is dd/1,mm/1,ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is dd/1,mmmm/100,0/1.

APP1-0003.Name: LongitudeRef
APP1-0003.Description: Indicates whether the longitude is east or west longitude. The ASCII value 'E' indicates east longitude, and 'W' is west longitude.

APP1-0004.Name: Longitude
APP1-0004.Description: Indicates the longitude. The longitude is expressed as three RATIONAL values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively. When degrees, minutes and seconds are expressed, the format is ddd/1,mm/1,ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is ddd/1,mmmm/100,0/1.

APP1-0006.Name: Altitude
APP1-0006.Description: Altitude, in meters, based on the reference altitude specified by GpsAltitudeRef.

APP1-0007.Name: TimeStamp
APP1-0007.Description: Time as coordinated universal time (UTC). The value is expressed as three rational numbers that give the hour, minute, and second.

APP1-0008.Name: Satellites
APP1-0008.Description: Specifies the GPS satellites used for measurements. This tag can be used to specify the ID number, angle of elevation, azimuth, SNR, and other information about each satellite. The format is not specified. If the GPS receiver is incapable of taking measurements, the value of the tag must be set to NULL.

APP1-0009.Name: Status
APP1-0009.Description: Specifies the status of the GPS receiver when the image is recorded. 'A' means measurement is in progress, and 'V' means the measurement is Interoperability.

APP1-000A.Name: MeasureMode
APP1-000A.Description: Specifies the GPS measurement mode. 2 specifies 2-D measurement, and 3 specifies 3-D measurement.

APP1-000B.Name: Dop
APP1-000B.Description: GPS DOP (data degree of precision). An HDOP value is written during 2-D measurement, and a PDOP value is written during 3-D measurement.

APP1-000C.Name: SpeedRef
APP1-000C.Description: Specifies the unit used to express the GPS receiver speed of movement. K , M , and N represent kilometers per hour, miles per hour, and knots respectively.

APP1-000D.Name: Speed
APP1-000D.Description: Speed of the GPS receiver movement.

APP1-000E.Name: TrackRef
APP1-000E.Description: Specifies the reference for giving the direction of GPS receiver movement. T specifies true direction, and M specifies magnetic direction.

APP1-000F.Name: Track
APP1-000F.Description: Direction of GPS receiver movement. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

APP1-0010.Name: ImgDirRef
APP1-0010.Description: Specifies the reference for the direction of the image when it is captured. T specifies true direction, and M specifies magnetic direction.

APP1-0011.Name: ImgDir
APP1-0011.Description: Direction of the image when it was captured. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

APP1-0012.Name: MapDatum
APP1-0012.Description: Indicates the geodetic survey data used by the GPS receiver. If the survey data is restricted to Japan, the value of this tag is 'TOKYO' or 'WGS-84'.

APP1-0013.Name: DestLatRef
APP1-0013.Description: Specifies whether the latitude of the destination point is north or south latitude. N specifies north latitude, and S specifies south latitude.

APP1-0014.Name: DestLat
APP1-0014.Description: Latitude of the destination point. The latitude is expressed as three rational values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds respectively. When degrees, minutes, and seconds are expressed, the format is dd/1, mm/1, ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is dd/1, mmmm/100, 0/1.

APP1-0015.Name: DestLongRef
APP1-0015.Description: Specifies whether the longitude of the destination point is east or west longitude. E specifies east longitude, and W specifies west longitude.

APP1-0016.Name: DestLong
APP1-0016.Description: Longitude of the destination point. The longitude is expressed as three rational values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds respectively. When degrees, minutes, and seconds are expressed, the format is ddd/1, mm/1, ss/1. When degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are given up to two decimal places, the format is ddd/1, mmmm/100, 0/1.

APP1-0017.Name: DestBearRef
APP1-0017.Description: Specifies the reference used for giving the bearing to the destination point. T specifies true direction, and M specifies magnetic direction.

APP1-0018.Name: DestBear
APP1-0018.Description: Bearing to the destination point. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

APP1-0019.Name: DestDistRef
APP1-0019.Description: Specifies the unit used to express the distance to the destination point. 'K', 'M', and 'N' represent kilometers, miles, and knots respectively.

APP1-00FE.Name: NewSubfileType
APP1-00FE.Description: Type of data in a subfile.

APP1-00FF.Name: SubfileType
APP1-00FF.Description: Type of data in a subfile.

APP1-0102.Name: BitsPerSample
APP1-0102.Description: Number of bits per color component.

APP1-0103.Name: Compression
APP1-0103.Description: Compression scheme used for the image data.

APP1-0106.Name: PhotometricInterp
APP1-0106.Description: How pixel data will be interpreted.

APP1-0107.Name: ThreshHolding
APP1-0107.Description: Technique used to convert from gray pixels to black and white pixels.

APP1-0108.Name: CellWidth
APP1-0108.Description: Width of the dithering or halftoning matrix.

APP1-0109.Name: CellHeight
APP1-0109.Description: Height of the dithering or halftoning matrix.

APP1-010A.Name: FillOrder
APP1-010A.Description: Logical order of bits in a byte.

APP1-010D.Name: DocumentName
APP1-010D.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the document from which the image was scanned.

APP1-010E.Name: ImageDescription
APP1-010E.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the title of the image.

APP1-010F.Name: EquipMake
APP1-010F.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the manufacturer of the equipment used to record the image.

APP1-0110.Name: EquipModel
APP1-0110.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the model name or model number of the equipment used to record the image.

APP1-0111.Name: StripOffsets
APP1-0111.Description: For each strip, the byte offset of that strip.

APP1-0112.Name: Orientation
APP1-0112.Description: Image orientation viewed in terms of rows and columns.

APP1-0115.Name: SamplesPerPixel
APP1-0115.Description: Number of color components per pixel.

APP1-0117.Name: StripBytesCount
APP1-0117.Description: For each strip, the total number of bytes in that strip.

APP1-0118.Name: MinSampleValue
APP1-0118.Description: For each color component, the minimum value assigned to that component.

APP1-0119.Name: MaxSampleValue
APP1-0119.Description: For each color component, the maximum value assigned to that component.

APP1-011A.Name: XResolution
APP1-011A.Description: Number of pixels per unit in the image width (x) direction. The unit is specified by ResolutionUnit.

APP1-011B.Name: YResolution
APP1-011B.Description: Number of pixels per unit in the image height (y) direction. The unit is specified by ResolutionUnit.

APP1-011C.Name: PlanarConfig
APP1-011C.Description: Whether pixel components are recorded in chunky or planar format.

APP1-011D.Name: PageName
APP1-011D.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the page from which the image was scanned.

APP1-011E.Name: XPosition
APP1-011E.Description: Offset from the left side of the page to the left side of the image. The unit of measure is specified by ResolutionUnit.

APP1-011F.Name: YPosition
APP1-011F.Description: Offset from the top of the page to the top of the image. The unit of measure is specified by ResolutionUnit.

APP1-0120.Name: FreeOffset
APP1-0120.Description: For each string of contiguous unused bytes, the byte offset of that string.

APP1-0121.Name: FreeByteCounts
APP1-0121.Description: For each string of contiguous unused bytes, the number of bytes in that string.

APP1-0122.Name: GrayResponseUnit
APP1-0122.Description: Precision of the number specified by GrayResponseCurve. 1 specifies tenths, 2 specifies hundredths, 3 specifies thousandths, and so on.

APP1-0123.Name: GrayResponseCurve
APP1-0123.Description: For each possible pixel value in a grayscale image, the optical density of that pixel value.

APP1-0124.Name: T4Option
APP1-0124.Description: Set of flags that relate to T4 encoding.

APP1-0125.Name: T6Option
APP1-0125.Description: Set of flags that relate to T6 encoding.

APP1-0128.Name: ResolutionUnit
APP1-0128.Description: Unit of measure for the horizontal resolution and the vertical resolution.

APP1-0129.Name: PageNumber
APP1-0129.Description: Page number of the page from which the image was scanned.

APP1-012D.Name: TransferFunction
APP1-012D.Description: Tables that specify transfer functions for the image.

APP1-0131.Name: SoftwareUsed
APP1-0131.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name and version of the software or firmware of the device used to generate the image.

APP1-0132.Name: DateTaken
APP1-0132.Description: Date and time the image was created.

APP1-013B.Name: Artist
APP1-013B.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the person who created the image.

APP1-013C.Name: HostComputer
APP1-013C.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the computer and/or operating system used to create the image.

APP1-013D.Name: Predictor
APP1-013D.Description: Type of prediction scheme that was applied to the image data before the encoding scheme was applied.

APP1-013E.Name: WhitePoint
APP1-013E.Description: Chromaticity of the white point of the image.

APP1-013F.Name: PrimaryChromaticities
APP1-013F.Description: For each of the three primary colors in the image, the chromaticity of that color.

APP1-0140.Name: ColorMap
APP1-0140.Description: Color palette (lookup table) for a palette-indexed image.

APP1-0141.Name: HalftoneHints
APP1-0141.Description: Information used by the halftone function

APP1-0142.Name: TileWidth
APP1-0142.Description: Number of pixel columns in each tile.

APP1-0143.Name: TileLength
APP1-0143.Description: Number of pixel rows in each tile.

APP1-0144.Name: TileOffset
APP1-0144.Description: For each tile, the byte offset of that tile.

APP1-0145.Name: TileByteCounts
APP1-0145.Description: For each tile, the number of bytes in that tile.

APP1-014C.Name: InkSet
APP1-014C.Description: Set of inks used in a separated image.

APP1-014D.Name: InkNames
APP1-014D.Description: Sequence of concatenated, null-terminated, character strings that specify the names of the inks used in a separated image.

APP1-0150.Name: DotRange
APP1-0150.Description: Color component values that correspond to a 0 percent dot and a 100 percent dot.

APP1-0151.Name: TargetPrinter
APP1-0151.Description: Null-terminated character string that describes the intended printing environment.

APP1-0152.Name: ExtraSamples
APP1-0152.Description: Number of extra color components. For example, one extra component might hold an alpha value.

APP1-0153.Name: SampleFormat
APP1-0153.Description: For each color component, the numerical format (unsigned, signed, floating point) of that component.

APP1-0154.Name: SMinSampleValue
APP1-0154.Description: For each color component, the minimum value of that component.

APP1-0155.Name: SMaxSampleValue
APP1-0155.Description: For each color component, the maximum value of that component.

APP1-0156.Name: TransferRange
APP1-0156.Description: Table of values that extends the range of the transfer function.

APP1-0201.Name: InterchangeFormat
APP1-0201.Description: Offset to the start of a JPEG bitstream.

APP1-0202.Name: InterchangeLength
APP1-0202.Description: Length, in bytes, of the JPEG bitstream.

APP1-0205.Name: LosslessPredictors
APP1-0205.Description: For each color component, a lossless predictor-selection value for that component.

APP1-0206.Name: PointTransforms
APP1-0206.Description: For each color component, a point transformation value for that component.

APP1-0207.Name: QTables
APP1-0207.Description: For each color component, the offset to the quantization table for that component.

APP1-0208.Name: DCTables
APP1-0208.Description: For each color component, the offset to the DC Huffman table (or lossless Huffman table) for that component.

APP1-0209.Name: ACTables
APP1-0209.Description: For each color component, the offset to the AC Huffman table for that component.

APP1-0211.Name: YCbCrCoefficients
APP1-0211.Description: Coefficients for transformation from RGB to YCbCr image data.

APP1-0212.Name: YCbCrSubsampling
APP1-0212.Description: Sampling ratio of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component.

APP1-0213.Name: YCbCrPositioning
APP1-0213.Description: Position of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component.

APP1-0214.Name: REFBlackWhite
APP1-0214.Description: Reference black point value and reference white point value.

APP1-0301.Name: Gamma
APP1-0301.Description: Gamma value attached to the image. The gamma value is stored as a rational number (pair of long) with a numerator of 100000. For example, a gamma value of 2.2 is stored as the pair (100000, 45455).

APP1-0302.Name: ICCProfileDescriptor
APP1-0302.Description: Null-terminated character string that identifies an ICC profile.

APP1-0303.Name: SRGBRenderingIntent
APP1-0303.Description: How the image should be displayed as defined by the International Color Consortium (ICC).

APP1-0320.Name: ImageTitle
APP1-0320.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the title of the image.

APP1-5001.Name: ResolutionXUnit
APP1-5001.Description: Units in which to display horizontal resolution.

APP1-5002.Name: ResolutionYUnit
APP1-5002.Description: Units in which to display vertical resolution.

APP1-5003.Name: ResolutionXLengthUnit
APP1-5003.Description: Units in which to display the image width.

APP1-5004.Name: ResolutionYLengthUnit
APP1-5004.Description: Units in which to display the image height.

APP1-5005.Name: PrintFlags
APP1-5005.Description: Sequence of one-byte Boolean values that specify printing options.

APP1-500A.Name: HalftoneLPI
APP1-500A.Description: Ink's screen frequency, in lines per inch.

APP1-500F.Name: HalftoneScreen
APP1-500F.Description: Boolean value that specifies whether to use the printer's default screens.

APP1-5010.Name: JPEGQuality
APP1-5010.Description: Private tag used by the Adobe Photoshop format. Not for public use.

APP1-5011.Name: GridSize
APP1-5011.Description: Block of information about grids and guides.

APP1-5013.Name: Width
APP1-5013.Description: Width, in pixels, of the thumbnail image.

APP1-5014.Name: Height
APP1-5014.Description: Height, in pixels, of the thumbnail image.

APP1-5015.Name: ColorDepth
APP1-5015.Description: bits per pixel (BPP) for the thumbnail image.

APP1-5016.Name: Planes
APP1-5016.Description: Number of color planes for the thumbnail image.

APP1-5017.Name: RawBytes
APP1-5017.Description: Byte offset between rows of pixel data.

APP1-5018.Name: Size
APP1-5018.Description: Total size, in bytes, of the thumbnail image.

APP1-5019.Name: CompressedSize
APP1-5019.Description: Compressed size, in bytes, of the thumbnail image.

APP1-501A.Name: ColorTransferFunction
APP1-501A.Description: Table of values that specify color transfer functions.

APP1-501B.Name: Data
APP1-501B.Description: Raw thumbnail bits in JPEG or RGB format. Depends on ThumbnailFormat.

APP1-5020.Name: ImageWidth
APP1-5020.Description: Number of pixels per row in the thumbnail image.

APP1-5021.Name: ImageHeight
APP1-5021.Description: Number of pixel rows in the thumbnail image.

APP1-5022.Name: BitsPerSample
APP1-5022.Description: Number of bits per color component in the thumbnail image.

APP1-5023.Name: Compression
APP1-5023.Description: Compression scheme used for thumbnail image data.

APP1-5024.Name: PhotometricInterp
APP1-5024.Description: How thumbnail pixel data will be interpreted.

APP1-5025.Name: ImageDescription
APP1-5025.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the title of the image.

APP1-5026.Name: EquipMake
APP1-5026.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the manufacturer of the equipment used to record the thumbnail image.

APP1-5027.Name: EquipModel
APP1-5027.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the model name or model number of the equipment used to record the thumbnail image.

APP1-5028.Name: StripOffsets
APP1-5028.Description: For each strip in the thumbnail image, the byte offset of that strip.

APP1-5029.Name: Orientation
APP1-5029.Description: Thumbnail image orientation in terms of rows and columns.

APP1-502A.Name: SamplesPerPixel
APP1-502A.Description: Number of color components per pixel in the thumbnail image.

APP1-502B.Name: RowsPerStrip
APP1-502B.Description: Number of rows per strip in the thumbnail image.

APP1-502C.Name: StripBytesCount
APP1-502C.Description: For each thumbnail image strip, the total number of bytes in that strip.

APP1-502D.Name: ResolutionX
APP1-502D.Description: Thumbnail resolution in the width direction. The resolution unit is given in ThumbnailResolutionUnit.

APP1-502E.Name: ResolutionY
APP1-502E.Description: Thumbnail resolution in the height direction. The resolution unit is given in ThumbnailResolutionUnit.

APP1-502F.Name: PlanarConfig
APP1-502F.Description: Whether pixel components in the thumbnail image are recorded in chunky or planar format.

APP1-5030.Name: ResolutionUnit
APP1-5030.Description: Unit of measure for the horizontal resolution and the vertical resolution of the thumbnail image.

APP1-5031.Name: TransferFunction
APP1-5031.Description: Tables that specify transfer functions for the thumbnail image.

APP1-5032.Name: SoftwareUsed
APP1-5032.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name and version of the software or firmware of the device used to generate the thumbnail image.

APP1-5033.Name: DateTime
APP1-5033.Description: Date and time the thumbnail image was created.

APP1-5034.Name: Artist
APP1-5034.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the name of the person who created the thumbnail image.

APP1-5035.Name: WhitePoint
APP1-5035.Description: Chromaticity of the white point of the thumbnail image.

APP1-5036.Name: PrimaryChromaticities
APP1-5036.Description: For each of the three primary colors in the thumbnail image, the chromaticity of that color.

APP1-5037.Name: YCbCrCoefficients
APP1-5037.Description: Coefficients for transformation from RGB to YCbCr data for the thumbnail image.

APP1-5038.Name: YCbCrSubsampling
APP1-5038.Description: Sampling ratio of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component for the thumbnail image.

APP1-5039.Name: YCbCrPositioning
APP1-5039.Description: Position of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component for the thumbnail image.

APP1-503A.Name: RefBlackWhite
APP1-503A.Description: Reference black point value and reference white point value for the thumbnail image.

APP1-503B.Name: CopyRight
APP1-503B.Description: Null-terminated character string that contains copyright information for the thumbnail image.

APP1-5090.Name: LuminanceTable
APP1-5090.Description: Luminance table. The luminance table and the chrominance table are used to control JPEG quality. A valid luminance or chrominance table has 64 entries of type Short. If an image has either a luminance table or a chrominance table, then it must have both tables.

APP1-5091.Name: ChrominanceTable
APP1-5091.Description: Chrominance table. The luminance table and the chrominance table are used to control JPEG quality. A valid luminance or chrominance table has 64 entries of type Short. If an image has either a luminance table or a chrominance table, then it must have both tables.

APP1-5100.Name: FrameDelay
APP1-5100.Description: Time delay, in hundredths of a second, between two frames in an animated GIF image.

APP1-5101.Name: LoopCount
APP1-5101.Description: For an animated GIF image, the number of times to display the animation. A value of 0 specifies that the animation should be displayed infinitely.

APP1-5111.Name: PixelPerUnitX
APP1-5111.Description: Pixels per unit in the x direction.

APP1-5112.Name: PixelPerUnitY
APP1-5112.Description: Pixels per unit in the y direction.

APP1-8298.Name: Copyright
APP1-8298.Description: Null-terminated character string that contains copyright information.

APP1-8769.Name: APP1
APP1-8769.Description: Private tag used by GDI+. Not for public use. GDI+ uses this tag to locate Exif-specific information.

APP1-8773.Name: ICCProfile
APP1-8773.Description: ICC profile embedded in the image.

APP1-8822.Name: ExposureProg
APP1-8822.Description: Class of the program used by the camera to set exposure when the picture is taken.

APP1-8824.Name: SpectralSense
APP1-8824.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies the spectral sensitivity of each channel of the camera used. The string is compatible with the standard developed by the ASTM Technical Committee.

APP1-8825.Name: GpsIFD
APP1-8825.Description: Offset to a block of GPS property items. Property items whose tags have the prefix Gps are stored in the GPS block. The GPS property items are defined in the IFD specification. GDI+ uses this tag to locate GPS information, but GDI+ does not expose this tag for public use.

APP1-8827.Name: ISOSpeed
APP1-8827.Description: ISO speed and ISO latitude of the camera or input device as specified in ISO 12232.

APP1-8828.Name: OECF
APP1-8828.Description: Optoelectronic conversion function (OECF) specified in ISO 14524. The OECF is the relationship between the camera optical input and the image values.

APP1-9000.Name: Ver
APP1-9000.Description: Version of the IFD standard supported. Nonexistence of this field is taken to mean nonconformance to the standard. Conformance to the standard is indicated by recording 0210 as a 4-byte ASCII string. Because the type is Undefined, there is no NULL terminator.

APP1-9003.Name: DTOrig
APP1-9003.Description: Date and time when the original image data was generated. For a DSC, the date and time when the picture was taken. The format is YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS with time shown in 24-hour format and the date and time separated by one blank character (0x2000). The character string length is 20 bytes including the NULL terminator. When the field is empty, it is treated as unknown.

APP1-9004.Name: DTDigitized
APP1-9004.Description: Date and time when the image was stored as digital data. If, for example, an image was captured by DSC and at the same time the file was recorded, then DateTimeOriginal and DateTimeDigitized will have the same contents. The format is YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS with time shown in 24-hour format and the date and time separated by one blank character (0x2000). The character string length is 20 bytes including the NULL terminator. When the field is empty, it is treated as unknown.

APP1-9101.Name: CompConfig
APP1-9101.Description: Information specific to compressed data. The channels of each component are arranged in order from the first component to the fourth. For uncompressed data, the data arrangement is given in the PhotometricInterp tag. However, because PhotometricInterp can only express the order of Y, Cb, and Cr, this tag is provided for cases when compressed data uses components other than Y, Cb, and Cr and to support other sequences.

APP1-9102.Name: CompBPP
APP1-9102.Description: Information specific to compressed data. The compression mode used for a compressed image is indicated in unit BPP.

APP1-9201.Name: ShutterSpeed
APP1-9201.Description: Shutter speed. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value.

APP1-9202.Name: Aperture
APP1-9202.Description: Lens aperture. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value.

APP1-9203.Name: Brightness
APP1-9203.Description: Brightness value. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value. Ordinarily it is given in the range of -99.99 to 99.99.

APP1-9204.Name: ExposureBias
APP1-9204.Description: Exposure bias. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value. Ordinarily it is given in the range -99.99 to 99.99.

APP1-9205.Name: MaxAperture
APP1-9205.Description: Smallest F number of the lens. The unit is the Additive System of Photographic Exposure (APEX) value. Ordinarily it is given in the range of 00.00 to 99.99, but it is not limited to this range.

APP1-9206.Name: SubjectDist
APP1-9206.Description: Distance to the subject, measured in meters.

APP1-9209.Name: Flash
APP1-9209.Description: Flash status. This tag is recorded when an image is taken using a strobe light (flash). Bit 0 indicates the flash firing status, and bits 1 and 2 indicate the flash return status.

APP1-920A.Name: FocalLength
APP1-920A.Description: Actual focal length, in millimeters, of the lens. Conversion is not made to the focal length of a 35 millimeter film camera.

APP1-9213.Name: ImageHistory
APP1-9213.Description: Record of what has been done to the image.

APP1-927C.Name: MakerNote
APP1-927C.Description: Note tag. A tag used by manufacturers of IFD writers to record information. The contents are up to the manufacturer.

APP1-9286.Name: UserComment
APP1-9286.Description: Comment tag. A tag used by IFD users to write keywords or comments about the image besides those in ImageDescription and without the character-code limitations of the ImageDescription tag.

APP1-9290.Name: DTSubsec
APP1-9290.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies a fraction of a second for the DateTime tag.

APP1-9291.Name: DTOrigSS
APP1-9291.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies a fraction of a second for the ExifDTOrig tag.

APP1-9292.Name: DTDigSS
APP1-9292.Description: Null-terminated character string that specifies a fraction of a second for the ExifDTDigitized tag.

APP1-9C9B.Name: XPTitle
APP1-9C9B.Description: Title tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

APP1-9C9C.Name: XPComment
APP1-9C9C.Description: Comment tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

APP1-9C9D.Name: XPAuthor
APP1-9C9D.Description: Author tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

APP1-9C9E.Name: XPKeywords
APP1-9C9E.Description: Keywords tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

APP1-9C9F.Name: XPSubject
APP1-9C9F.Description: Subject tag used by Windows, encoded in UCS2

APP1-A000.Name: FPXVer
APP1-A000.Description: FlashPix format version supported by an FPXR file. If the FPXR function supports FlashPix format version 1.0, this is indicated similarly to ExifVer by recording 0100 as a 4-byte ASCII string. Because the type is Undefined, there is no NULL terminator.

APP1-A001.Name: ColorSpace
APP1-A001.Description: Color space specifier. Normally sRGB (=1) is used to define the color space based on the PC monitor conditions and environment. If a color space other than sRGB is used, Uncalibrated (=0xFFFF) is set. Image data recorded as Uncalibrated can be treated as sRGB when it is converted to FlashPix.

APP1-A002.Name: PixXDim
APP1-A002.Description: Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid width of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag, whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should not exist in an uncompressed file.

APP1-A003.Name: PixYDim
APP1-A003.Description: Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid height of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should not exist in an uncompressed file. Because data padding is unnecessary in the vertical direction, the number of lines recorded in this valid image height tag will be the same as that recorded in the SOF.

APP1-A004.Name: RelatedWav
APP1-A004.Description: The name of an audio file related to the image data. The only relational information recorded is the IFD audio file name and extension (an ASCII string that consists of 8 characters plus a period (.), plus 3 characters). The path is not recorded. When you use this tag, audio files must be recorded in conformance with the IFD audio format. Writers can also store audio data within APP2 as FlashPix extension stream data.

APP1-A005.Name: Interop
APP1-A005.Description: Offset to a block of property items that contain interoperability information.

APP1-A20B.Name: FlashEnergy
APP1-A20B.Description: Strobe energy, in Beam Candle Power Seconds (BCPS), at the time the image was captured.

APP1-A20C.Name: SpatialFR
APP1-A20C.Description: Camera or input device spatial frequency table and SFR values in the image width, image height, and diagonal direction, as specified in ISO 12233.

APP1-A20E.Name: FocalXRes
APP1-A20E.Description: Number of pixels in the image width (x) direction per unit on the camera focal plane. The unit is specified in ExifFocalResUnit.

APP1-A20F.Name: FocalYRes
APP1-A20F.Description: Number of pixels in the image height (y) direction per unit on the camera focal plane. The unit is specified in ExifFocalResUnit.

APP1-A210.Name: FocalResUnit
APP1-A210.Description: Unit of measure for ExifFocalXRes and ExifFocalYRes.

APP1-A214.Name: SubjectLoc
APP1-A214.Description: Location of the main subject in the scene. The value of this tag represents the pixel at the center of the main subject relative to the left edge. The first value indicates the column number, and the second value indicates the row number.

APP1-A215.Name: ExposureIndex
APP1-A215.Description: Exposure index selected on the camera or input device at the time the image was captured.

APP1-A217.Name: SensingMethod
APP1-A217.Description: Image sensor type on the camera or input device.

APP1-A300.Name: FileSource
APP1-A300.Description: The image source. If a DSC recorded the image, the value of this tag is 3.

APP1-A301.Name: SceneType
APP1-A301.Description: The type of scene. If a DSC recorded the image, the value of this tag must be set to 1, indicating that the image was directly photographed.

APP1-A302.Name: CfaPattern
APP1-A302.Description: The color filter array (CFA) geometric pattern of the image sensor when a one-chip color area sensor is used. It does not apply to all sensing methods.
